Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Drain and rinse the @black beans{1%can} in a #sieve{}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{90%g}. Chop the @medium tomato{1} into 1cm pieces.

Chop the @sweet potatoes{2} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Pop onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, if you'd like, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast the sweet potatoes on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, pop the chopped tomato into a large #bowl{} with a drizzle of oil. Season with salt, pepper and a pinch of @?sugar{}, if you'd like, then set aside.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat.

When hot, add the garlic, @tomato puree{30%g} and @Mexican style spice mix{1}. 

> TIP: Use less spice if you'd like things milder.

Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pop the black beans into a bowl and roughly mash with the back of a #fork{} or #potato masher{}. Stir the mashed beans, @water{100%ml} and @vegetable stock paste{10%g} into the pan, then simmer until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Taste and season with salt and pepper if you'd like.

When the refried beans have thickened, remove from the heat.

Divide the beans between the centre of each @super soft tortillas{4}(whole wheat) (2 per person) and top with the cheese. Roll up tightly - these are your 'black hole' flautas! Place the flautas onto a lightly oiled baking tray, seam-side down, leaving a small space between each. Drizzle with a little oil, then bake on the middle shelf of your oven until golden, ~{10-15%minutes}.

> Space Ranger Mission: Brace yourselves! Little space rangers can help make the 'black hole' flautas by adding in the fillings and rolling them up. Reserve some cheese for sprinkling over the top before baking if you'd like to make them look extra dark inside.

When everything is almost ready, add the @wild rocket{40%g} to the tomato bowl and toss to coat.

When ready, plate up your 'black hole' flautas with the roasted sweet potatoes and rocket salad alongside. Serve with a dollop of @Greek style natural yoghurt{50%g} on the side for dipping. Enjoy!